# Core constraints

This project reimplements Wikipedia's Vector 2022 skin as a static Hugo theme, plus a
MediaWiki-style Infobox shortcode. It never depends on a MediaWiki server, PHP, or a
database.

- No code file (JS, TS, CSS/SCSS, HTML/Go-template) exceeds **500–1000 lines**. Split
  before hitting the ceiling, not after.
- Never mix languages in one file — no inline `<style>`/`<script>` in templates.
- One concern per file: one component per CSS file, one behavior per TS module, one page
  region per partial.
- Every shortcode lives in its own folder: `layouts/_shortcodes/{name}/{file}.html`, even
  if currently a single file.
- The built `public/` output must run with zero JS runtime dependencies beyond the
  browser — `node_modules/` is dev-tooling only.
- If a task would require violating any of the above, stop and flag it rather than
  silently exceeding the limit.

Full rationale: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` in this repo.
